Q. CVS Health is trying to better understand its pharmacy sales, and how well different products are selling. Each drug can only be produced by one manufacturer.

Write a query to find the top 3 most profitable drugs sold, and how much profit they made. Assume that there are no ties in the profits. Display the result from the highest to the lowest total profit.

Definition:

cogs stands for Cost of Goods Sold which is the direct cost associated with producing the drug.
Total Profit = Total Sales - Cost of Goods Sold


A.
Method 1:
WITH SALES AS 
(
  SELECT DRUG,
  SUM(TOTAL_SALES - COGS) AS TOTAL_PROFIT 
  FROM pharmacy_sales
  GROUP BY DRUG
)
SELECT DRUG, TOTAL_PROFIT FROM SALES
ORDER BY TOTAL_PROFIT DESC
LIMIT 3
;

Method 2:
WITH SALES AS (
  SELECT DRUG, SUM(TOTAL_SALES - COGS) AS TOTAL_PROFIT
  FROM pharmacy_sales
  GROUP BY DRUG
)
SELECT DRUG, TOTAL_PROFIT 
FROM (
  SELECT DRUG, TOTAL_PROFIT, 
  ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY TOTAL_PROFIT DESC) AS RN
  FROM SALES
) RANKED
WHERE RN <= 3;


Method 3:
SELECT DRUG, TOTAL_SALES - COGS AS TOTAL_PROFIT FROM pharmacy_sales
ORDER BY TOTAL_PROFIT DESC
LIMIT 3;
